[1mMethod Interpretation:[0m
  A (Additive)       : Norm grows with α. At large α, activation drifts off the
                       RMSNorm shell. Risk: gibberish if norm expansion > ~50%.
  B (NormPreserving) : Norm locked; pure direction shift. Equivalent to A at
                       small α (small-angle approx: ‖v‖·α/‖h‖ << 1).
                       At large α, B is strictly weaker (same direction change,
                       no magnitude boost), so needs larger α to match A's effect.
  C (Angular)        : Identical to B in effect but parameterised by rotation angle.
                       θ saturates at 90° — impossible to 'flip' h past v̂.
                       Most conservative; most norm-stable by design.

